18. **North Harris (Tarbert):** The Harris congregation was well-established by 1896. A stone church, built with local materials, was erected at the Tarbert station around 1897. Additional stations were maintained at Kyles Stockinish and Kyles Scalpay in the northern part of the island, as well as at Finsbay, Stronde, and Obbe in the south. Harris was formally constituted as a charge in 1901.
